HEADWORD: Sweaty
<hw>Sweat"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Sweatier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Sweatiest</adjf>.]</amorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Moist with sweat;
<as>as, a <ex>sweaty</ex> skin; a <ex>sweaty</ex>
garment.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Consisting of sweat; of the nature of
sweat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>No noisome whiffs or <qex>sweaty</qex> streams.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Causing sweat; hence, laborious; toilsome;
difficult.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>sweaty</xex> forge.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Prior.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swede</ent>⟦br⟧
